The **Ramayana** being written by a prince (Valmiki) challenges the idea of strict caste-based authorship, as it suggests mobility or flexibility in social roles beyond rigid economic constraints. While the text itself upholds caste hierarchy, the authorship itself does not reinforce the argument that caste rigidly determined all social functions.
